Good, everything is clean now. Let me start fresh.

The connection is being made but the remote side closes immediately. The issue is that socat forks a new connection each time, but the inner socat to port 6666 connects to the qemu serial telnet which is `nowait` - it only accepts connections when a client connects. But the problem might be that the inner socat connects and disconnects too quickly. Let me try a different approach - use a single socat that directly bridges.



